# Keep the Docker build context lean (#176). The daemon image build needs
# schema/ + server/ (deploy/docker/Dockerfile COPY lines); the meridian-db image
# (deploy/docker/Dockerfile.db) also needs the db-init wrappers (deploy/docker/
# db-init) AND — for its #482 world-CONTENT emit stage — the mcc compiler source
# (tools/mcc) plus the content tree (content/). Everything else is excluded so it
# neither bloats the context nor invalidates the build cache.
.git
.github
client
!client
client/godot-cpp
docs
tests
scripts
# tools/ is excluded EXCEPT tools/mcc — the meridian-db content stage (#482)
# builds mcc there to emit the world CONTENT DML. `tools/*` (not `tools`) leaves
# the tools dir itself un-excluded so `!tools/mcc` can re-include that subtree.
tools/*
!tools/mcc
# content/ IS shipped (the meridian-db content stage compiles it into world DB
# DML). Daemon images do not COPY it, so it only affects the db-image context.
deploy
!deploy/docker/db-init
*.md
uv.lock
pyproject.toml

# Never ship build trees or local certs into an image context.
**/build/
server/build/
tools/mcc/build/
deploy/docker/certs/*.crt
deploy/docker/certs/*.key
deploy/docker/certs/*.pem
# Rendered audio (gitignored dev artifacts) is not needed by the world-DB emit.
content/**/*.wav

# Editor / OS noise
.DS_Store
__pycache__/
*.pyc
